Duly accomplished time record of recipients of COVID-19 AHDP and SRA; and

Accomplishment Report for the Job Order and BHWs personnel.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor issue a new Executive Order appointing or designating at least five but not more than seven members to the BAC as set forth under Section 11.2.1 of the 2016 RIRR of RA 9184.

Further, we recommended that the BAC:

Include in the Annual Procurement Plan (APP) the PPAs to be procured during the year with the appropriate mode of procurement;

Require the suppliers for subsequent procurement through Negotiated Procurement-Emergency Cases to submit the mandatory documentary requirements, i.e. Mayor’s/Business Permit, Income/Business Tax Return (For ABCs 500k above) and Omnibus Sworn Statement, before issuance of Notice of Award, otherwise, the transactions shall be suspended in audit;

Require the BAC Secretariat, to post in the PhilGEPS website the Notice of Award, Contract or Purchase Order and Notice to Proceed.

We also recommended that the General Services Officer refrain from signing the Purchase Order/Contract in behalf of the Municipality without an appropriate authority from the HoPE.

